One-compartment and two-compartment distribution models were considered. To obtain estimates of the total IgG level, which is the sum of endogenous IgG and IVIg-derived IgG, we incorporated the endogenous IgG production as a baseline concentration (CBAS) in the model. Patients with CIDP have a higher steady-state baseline IgG level because of prolonged maintenance treatment. The typical value for CBAS and the effect of disease type were included in the base model according to the following equation:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
